  "summary": "Following the sounds of scratching, Dr. Castells and Sattler discover a chair outside Lady Cammichael's room that has been torn into strips by cat claws. When Dr. Castells attempts to warn Lady Cammichael, she dismisses the incident as a prank and refuses to provide information. To ensure her safety, Dr. Castells and Sattler search her room and agree to patrol the path to the house in shifts.\n\nThat night, Dr. Castells dreams of a gray cat leading him to a specific spot in a study. Upon investigating the study the next morning, he finds the room matches his dream, where he discovers a missing book and a small scrap of paper caught on a nail reading, \"That cat...\" Later, while in the green sitting room, Arthur Carmichael reacts to a mouse running across the floor with extreme, trembling terror, leading to a realization for Dr. Castells.\n\nDuring the night, Sattler discovers that Lady Cammichael is locked in her room and hears fierce mewling alongside a piercing scream from Mrs. Carruthers. Dr. Castells and Sattler break down the door to find Lady Cammichael on her bed, bleeding from severe claw marks on her throat. After bandaging her wounds, Dr. Castells sends a telegram to a hospital nurse. The following morning, Dr. Castells and Sattler dig under a sycamore tree and unearth the body of a cat that has been dead for a week. Sattler identifies the presence of hydrogen cyanide on the carcass.",
